Hi  Tianchun Luo, Yes, you can use the HubL code to access and use the data filled in the user form in HubSpot. To access the data filled in a user form, you can use the form object in HubL. The form object contains all the fields and their values submitted in the form. You can access the values of individual fields using the form. field name syntax, where the field name is the name of the form field. Here is an example - &lt;!-- HubL template code --&gt;
{% set form_data = form %}
&lt;h1&gt;Thank you for submitting the form!&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your name is {{ form_data.name }} and your email is {{ form_data.email }}.&lt;/p&gt;
